<p style=""><font face="-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, Segoe UI, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 15px;">Expandcart platform has a variety of payment methods available on your store which are divided into 5 categories as follows:</span></font></p><p style=""><strong style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">(Accept Credit Cards,&nbsp;Manual Payments,&nbsp;Accept PayPal,&nbsp;Prepaid Cards, Mobile Payment)</strong><span style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">&nbsp;</span><br></p><p style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">You can activate an account on any portal and enter your account data on the payment method in the control panel of your store, to access the payment settings <a href="/admin/extension/payment" target="_blank">Click Here</a></p><h2 style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 22px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); letter-spacing: normal;"><strong>Credit Cards</strong></h2><p style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">To accept online payment by Visa, Master card ... etc. You need to open an account on one of the payment gateways such ( Paytabs, Payfort, 2checkout, Stripe,.. etc). All you need to do is open the account at the payment gateway then link your account with your store from the payment setting.</p><h2 style="margin-top: 0px;"><strong style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: normal;">PayPal</strong></h2><p style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;">It is the fastest and safest way to send money, pay online, receive money, or set up a merchant account. It allows the user to transfer money online and email to different addresses. The user can also send money to others or transfer it to a bank account. There are two types of PayPal accounts:</p><p style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;"><strong>Payments Standard :&nbsp;</strong></p><div class="caption" style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 15px;"><p>Accept credit cards and PayPal on your website easily and securely. PayPal is accepted worldwide and is very easy to use especially if you have no experience with online payments, In order to open an account please click on the link below:&nbsp;</p><p><a href="https://www.paypal.com/eg/merchantsignup/applicationChecklist?signupType=CREATE_NEW_ACCOUNT&amp;productIntentId=wp_standard&amp;Z3JncnB0=" style="color: rgb(2, 99, 143);" target="_blank">https://www.paypal.com/eg/merchantsignup/applicationChecklist?signupType=CREATE_NEW_ACCOUNT&amp;productIntentId=wp_standard&amp;Z3JncnB0=</a></p><p><strong>Payments Express:&nbsp;</strong></p><div class="caption"></div><p>Express Checkout is a great addition to your online shopping cart. Get paid quickly with PayPal today.<br></p><div class="caption"><p>Give your customers the fastest ordering experience ever, they do not need to fill in any details, just sign in to their PayPal account, and press the Pay button.</p><p>In order to create an account you can visit the following link and follow the steps required knowing that you can create an account individual or company:</p><p><a href="https://www.paypal.com/ee/webapps/mpp/account-selection" style="color: rgb(2, 99, 143);">https://www.paypal.com/ee/webapps/mpp/account-selection</a></p><h2 style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 22px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); letter-spacing: normal;"><strong>Manual Payments&nbsp;</strong></h2><p><strong>Bank Transfer :&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Accept payments through a bank transfer to your account.&nbsp;In this way, you put your bank account data and when the customer selects at the checkout page this payment method will be showing with him your bank account and able transferred to it.</p><p><strong>Cheque or Purchase Order :&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Accept payments through a banking check or a certified purchase order.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Cash on Delivery :&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Accept payments in cash when you deliver the products to your customers. If your store customer selects this payment method, they should pay for the order not when it is placed, but when it is delivered.</p><p><strong>Free Checkout :&nbsp;</strong></p><div class="caption"><p>The order will be made without payment from the customers side.</p><h2 style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.53846; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 0px; font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: normal;"><strong>Prepaid Cards</strong></h2><div><p>Some providers are offering this service such ( CashU, OneCard, Zain Cash)</p><h2 style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.53846; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); margin-top: 0px; font-size: 22px; letter-spacing: normal;"><strong>Mobile Payment</strong></h2><div><p>By using a mobile service provider to pay the order like (MobiPay)</p></div></div></div></div></div>
';

